1.title: The Fastest Feet
1.plot: The Floyd Little Double Dutch team's title as world champions is challenged this week when they face long-time rival Kandie's Rope Twisters from Washington DC. Floyd Little's Coach Quaniee has serious history with Coach Bradshaw of the Kandie Rope Twisters and now they're passing that rivalry on to their young daughters, who will battle each other head-to-head in an epic speed competition for the title of the fastest feet. Will Floyd Little have what it takes to bring home first place?

2.title: Tricks of the Trade
2.plot: This week, Floyd Little prepares to face their toughest competition yet--the Jazzy Jumpers from Brooklyn. With such a tough opponent ahead of them, Floyd Little needs to amp up their freestyle routine in order to ensure a win--which means adding an incredibly difficult trick to their already demanding performance. Will they be able to master this trick in time or will this big risk mean big failure for our squad?

3.title: Double Trouble
3.plot: When coach Laila decides to sign the team up for something new--a doubles competition--it causes a rift between the Floyd Little coaches. To make matters worse, they know nothing about the team they're going up against, the Swagga Jumpers from Brooklyn. As the team continues to struggle in practice, will Floyd Little face the possibility of having their first loss?

imdb.plot outline: Double Dutch jump rope is a classic school yard favorite but Double Dutch today is an international competitive sport that is filled with tricks, turns, tears and triumphs. In this series, we'll focus on the coaches, moms and kids from FloydLittle's, one of the hottest and best jump roping teams in the country.
